                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p rend=\"align(right)\"><placeName>Pto Cabello</placeName>, <date>12<hi rend=\"sup\"\n                        >th</hi> Febr 1855</date></p>\n            <p>\n                <addressee>Isaac Leeser Esq.</addressee>\n            </p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">\n                <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>\n            </p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(2)\">Dear sir,</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(3)\">My last respects to you was<lb/> on the <date>22<hi rend=\"sup\"\n                        >nd</hi> September</date> last, but I wrote you pre<lb/>-viously regarding\n                our brethren in <placeName>Jerusalem</placeName> statg<lb/> that the few hebrews\n                that are established here showed<lb/> a willingness in contributing with their might\n                in<lb/> behalf of our above mentioned brethren, but they wai<lb/>ted the arrival\n                from the <placeName>Interior</placeName> of <persName>Mr David Lobo</persName><lb/>\n                to meet for the purport. I had to leave for <placeName>Curacao</placeName><lb/> as I\n                have written you, and on my departure I reques<lb/>ted an acquaintance that when the\n                meeting took<lb/> place, he would oblige me by including my name<lb/> on the list\n                for two pounds sterling. I returned here<lb/> last month together with my family and\n                after<lb/> having been here for a few days, I <sic>enquired</sic> whether<lb/> any\n                thing had been done, and regret to say that<lb/> the answer I got was a\n                negative.</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">The Calender you sent me was received here<lb/> during my absence,\n                but without any of your com<lb/>munication.</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">I <sic>inclose</sic> a draft on <persName>Messrs. Dallett\n                    Brothers</persName><lb/> for twenty dollars. Please pay yourself for the\n                Cal<lb/>ender, my contribution for the next year of your<lb/> Occident and for a\n                daily prayer book in herew<lb/> and german, that I will thank you to send me<lb/> by\n                first opportunity. The remainder is for your bre</p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3r20sg85/canvas/p1"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
